						<summary>

						<p>In the same place as above.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-NArāyaṇadēva: Year 8</hi><note n="146-2">The year has been doubtfully read as [2nd in <hi rend="italic">A.R.S.I.E.,</hi> 1909].</note><hi rend="bold">= 1146-47 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamp to an Īśvara temple (name lost) and a <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamp to the temple of Ammaḍēśvara and two <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> of money (to provide oil for the lamps) by a certain merchant named Kaṇḍan Āṇḍammai of Kaṇṇāḍiputtūr in Karaivaḻi-nāḍu. </p>						

